data <- read.csv("MetabolomicsAndGenetics_4Praktikum.data.tsv", sep = "\t", header = T)
data$GENDER <- ifelse(data$GENDER == "male", 1, 2)
data[,4:154] <- lapply(data[,4:154], log2)
data <- data %>%
  mutate(across(4:154, ~ {
    m  <- mean(., na.rm = TRUE)
    s  <- sd(., na.rm = TRUE)
    l <- m - 3 * s
    h <- m + 3 * s
    ifelse(. < l | . > h, NA, .)
  }))

2

a,b

valid_cols <- sapply(data, function(x) sum(!is.na(x)) >= 500)
df_filtered <- data[, valid_cols]
snp_cols <- colnames(data)[startsWith(colnames(data), "SNP")]
met_cols <- df_filtered %>%
  select(-Person, -GENDER, -AGE, -starts_with("SNP")) %>%
  colnames()
results <- list()
min_n <- 500
for (met in met_cols) {
  for (snp in snp_cols) {

    df_sub <- df_filtered %>%
      transmute(
        AGE      = AGE,
        GENDER   = GENDER,
        genotype = .data[[snp]],
        con      = .data[[met]]
      )

    n_nonmiss <- sum(complete.cases(df_sub))

    if (n_nonmiss < min_n) next

    fit <- lm(con ~ genotype + AGE + GENDER, data = df_sub)

    res <- broom::tidy(fit) %>%
      mutate(
        metabolite = met,
        SNP        = snp,
        n          = n_nonmiss
      )

    results[[paste(met, snp, sep = "_")]] <- res
  }
}

results_df <- bind_rows(results)

c, d

geno_effects <- results_df %>%
  filter(term == "genotype") %>%
  select(metabolite, SNP, estimate, std.error, p.value, n)

n_tests   <- nrow(geno_effects)
alpha_bonf <- 0.05 / n_tests

geno_sig <- geno_effects %>%
  filter(p.value <= alpha_bonf)

geno_sig_sorted <- geno_sig %>%
  arrange(SNP, p.value)

3

top_hits <- geno_sig_sorted %>%
  group_by(SNP) %>%
  slice_min(p.value, n = 1, with_ties = FALSE) %>%
  ungroup()

for (i in seq_len(nrow(top_hits))) {
  met <- top_hits$metabolite[i]
  snp <- top_hits$SNP[i]

  df_plot <- df_filtered %>%
    transmute(
      genotype = .data[[snp]],
      con      = .data[[met]],
      sex      = GENDER
    ) %>%
    filter(!is.na(genotype), !is.na(con), !is.na(sex))

  boxplot(con ~ genotype, data = df_plot,
          main = paste(met, "vs", snp),
          xlab = "Genotype",
          ylab = paste("Concentration of", met))

  cols_sex <- ifelse(df_plot$sex == levels(factor(df_plot$sex))[1], "red", "blue")

  beeswarm(con ~ genotype,
           data = df_plot,
           pch  = 19,
           pwcol = cols_sex,
           xlab = "Genotype",
           ylab = paste("Concentration of", met),
           main = paste(met, "vs", snp))
  legend("topright",
         legend = levels(factor(df_plot$sex)),
         col    = c("red", "blue"),
         pch    = 19)
}
